Submission Requirements
You must submit the following in the Assignment link provided in Google Classroom (GCR):
   PPT Presentation (as per format below)
   Base Paper (PDF copy)
Base Paper Selection
The base paper should meet the following conditions:
Published from 2020 onwards (2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, or later).
Must be indexed in Scopus OR SCI/SCIE journals.
Should be relevant to the course syllabus: Machine Learning Essentials.
PPT Guidelines (for Zeroth Review)
Your PPT should contain the following slides:
Slide 1: Title of the Project, Name, Roll No., Course Details.
Slide 2: Abstract (from the base paper in your own words).
         Link to the Base Paper (Publisher link, not Google Drive).
         Dataset Information (Name, Source/Link, Features, Size).
Slide 3: Literature Review (summary of 3–4 related papers with year & source).
Slide 4: Proposed Workflow/Block Diagram of your approach.
Slide 5: Programming Language / Tools / Frameworks chosen for implementation.
Slide 6: References (IEEE format – include base paper and other references).
Evaluation Criteria
Relevance of base paper to syllabus.
Quality of PPT presentation.
Proper citation and references.
Clarity of workflow and methodology.
Deadline
Submit your PPT and base paper only through the GCR Assignment link before
the deadline.
